\begin_layout Subsubsection
Permutator and hom-associator
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\series bold
permutator 
\series default
is the quadlinear map 
\begin_inset Formula $[\cdot,\cdot,\cdot,\cdot]_{f,\mu}\colon A^{4}\to A$
\end_inset

 defined by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
[a,b,c,d]_{f,\mu}=f(ab)(f(c)f(d))-(f(a)f(b))f(cd)
\]

\end_inset

for all 
\begin_inset Formula $a,b,c,d\in A$
\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 are understood from context, then we simplify notation by writing 
\begin_inset Formula $[\cdot,\cdot,\cdot,\cdot]=[\cdot,\cdot,\cdot,\cdot]_{f,\mu}$
\end_inset

.
 The 
\series bold
hom-associator 
\series default
is the trilinear map 
\begin_inset Formula $[\cdot,\cdot,\cdot]_{f,\mu}\colon A^{3}\to A$
\end_inset

 defined by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
[a,b,c]_{f,\mu}=(ab)f(c)-f(a)(bc)
\]

\end_inset

for all 
\begin_inset Formula $a,b,c\in A$
\end_inset

.
 The permutator can be expressed in terms of the hom-associator as follows:
 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $a,b,c,d\in A$
\end_inset

, we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
[a,b,c,d]=f^{2}(a)[b,c,d]-[ab,f(c),f(d)]+[f(a),bc,f(d)]-[f(a),f(b),cd]+[a,b,c]f^{2}(d).
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

